# hooks
- label: --json create, --json set, --json unset, --json rm, --json link, and --json unlink mutations whose matching Hook fails or times out after the Store mutation commits exit non-zero, leave stdout empty, report the committed Hook failure or timeout on stderr, and persist both the Store mutation and Hook Run
  id: jhf
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh json_mutation_hook_failure_or_timeout_reports_committed_without_success_json
  tags: [implemented]
- label: --json create, --json set, and --json link mutations with multiple matching Hooks run matching Hooks sequentially after commit; when one or more earlier Hooks succeed and a later Hook fails or times out, the mutation remains committed, the successful and failing or timed-out Hook Runs persist, later matching Hooks do not run, stdout stays empty, and stderr reports the committed Hook failure or timeout
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh json_multiple_matching_hooks_stop_after_failure_or_timeout
  tags: [implemented]
